  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: Subsequent to the original validation campaign (completed Q3 2023), the intended use was extended to include a paediatric sub-population (body surface area < 0.7 m², flow rates 0.8–1.5 L/min) following an expanded regulatory submission in Q1 2025. The assessment team determined that the existing validation dataset, collected at adult flow rates of 2.5–6.0 L/min, provides sufficient coverage by interpolation of the power-law hemolysis model, and no additional validation experiments were commissioned for the paediatric regime.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
