      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) match simulation inputs within ±3%.",
      "rationale": "All five adult validation experiments were conducted with controlled inlet flow rates (±1.2%), rotational speed (±0.5%), temperature (37 ± 0.5 °C), and hematocrit (33 ± 1%). Traceability to NIST-calibrated instrumentation confirmed. Test conditions cover adult operating envelope only; no paediatric bench experiments were performed."
