      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH, RH index) directly maps to clinical hemolysis outcome measure.",
      "rationale": "Normalised index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index are established surrogate endpoints for device-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance. QoI relevance is maintained for both adult and paediatric populations since the same biochemical damage mechanism applies; however, the quantitative mapping has not been independently validated at paediatric flow rates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same pump geometry, fluid analogue, and operating regime as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry with porcine blood analogue at adult CPB flow conditions. The assessment team judged that the power-law hemolysis model's parametric sensitivity analyses within the adult dataset provide sufficient basis to assert coverage of the paediatric sub-population added to the COU in Q1 2025, citing monotonic scaling of shear exposure with flow rate. No new validation activities were commissioned to substantiate this extension; the achieved level is therefore claimed on the basis of the original 2023 campaign alone."
    },
    {
